<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5241c</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-08T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4958. Ask British authorities to ascertain if Reuter or any other
                                news organization has forwarded presidential communication to Russia
                                to any other country or agency, to be held for release. If so, have
                                Reuter or other agency recall all copies. The message is in the
                                hands of Reuter through an error here. The communication will not be
                                published until certain important alterations are made.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>